properties.Special Notes: "New parcels proposed for any purpose other than agriculture, forestry, recreation, or conservation shall demonstrate location for wastewater disposal (sewer hook up or on-site), water supply, other utilities, and a building envelope where some structure could be located that meets all slope, setback, and buffer requirements" (page 3-93). Mobile home parks are allowed in places that don't have a two-story minimum requirement. I figure out which don't have this requirement by seeing where cottage developments (2 stories max) are permitted.
properties.Tooltip Notes: Cottage and Conservation PUDs permitted. "PUD requiring land conservation" applies only to Conservation PUDs.

properties.ADU Min. Parking Spaces Units: Parking Spaces Add'l to Main Unit
properties.Special Notes: PUD *may* require land conservation, may =/= will. All developments >2 units require site plan approval, *major* site plan approval requires public hearings. Major site plans include construction of new principal buildings. So, any building with >2 units requires a public hearing. "New parcels proposed for any purpose other than agriculture, forestry, recreation, or conservation shall demonstrate location for wastewater disposal (sewer hook up or on-site), water supply, other utilities, and a building envelope where some structure could be located that meets all slope, setback, and buffer requirements" (page 3-93). Minimum unit size for hotel guest rooms is 220sqft, but for residential units it is unstated.
